The nearest airport is the Kansas City International Airport (MCI) which is about 40 miles north of Olathe. All the major rental car companies are available at the Airport.
The taxi to Olathe costs between $82 - $90. There are (free)telephones near the baggage carousels which can be used to call a cab.

For fine dining, it may be easier to go to Kansas City, though Oklahoma Joe's is well renowned. There are good restaurants in Overland Park as well.

Olathe has a number of hotels including all the major hotels. These include Hampton Inn, Residence Inn and Fairfield Inn on South Strangline Road.These are all right next to each other.Rates vary between $ 90 to $ 169 per night.Wifi is free in all these hotels. All of them have a good breakfast which opens at 6:30 am.There is a heated pool and a few treadmills for fitness. There are a number of chain restaurats within a half mile from any of these hotels.
There is also a La Quinta Inn on West 151st Street, about a mile down the road from these hotels.
For budget travellers, there is an Econo Lodge
with rooms at $ 50 a night. This is approxiately 3.5 miles south of the hotel on S Strangline Road.
